{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place dark chocolate in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>Turbo\/1 sec\/2-3 times<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place milk, cream, sugar and egg yolks in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>8 min\/90°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add peppermint extract and food colouring, if using, then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Pour into a shallow freezer proof container and freeze for at least 8 hours until solid.","To serve, remove from freezer, tip out and cut into squares (3 cm x 3 cm). Place half the frozen squares in mixing bowl and churn <nobr>20 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>, then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer to a serving bowl.","Place remaining squares in mixing bowl and churn <nobr>20 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>, then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer to serving bowl. Add reserved chocolate chip pieces and fold through before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g dark chocolate, cut in pieces (1 cm)","300 g whole milk","450 g double cream","150 g granulated sugar","5 egg yolks, from large eggs","1 ½ tsp peppermint extract","3 drops green food colouring              (optional)"]}],"id":"r97863","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-7ZlEImTXm30\/XZaoZT_c6NI\/AAAAAAAAhJ0\/dGsnlPwsdqItvwx6mZX1-7wVyZIAz4C0ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_npfTnj6ZvAuq87xG.png","title":"Mint Choc Chip","publishedAt":"2015-09-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.1 g","fat":"39.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"39 g","calories":"2239 kJ \/ 535 kcal"},"usefulItems":"freezer proof container, long sharp knife, serving bowl, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["If using fresh mint this should be added with milk and cream. Pass through a sieve before transferring to freezer proof container.","Freeze the ice cream mixture in ice cube trays rather than cutting into squares if preferred."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","8h 20m","8 portions"]}